{
  "stem": "802.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know if you ever heard about Janusz Korczak, whom we saw all the time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a physician, and he also was a writer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was in the orphanage with the children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, ultimately, he was led to the gas chamber with the children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even though people pleaded with him to leave the Warsaw Ghetto-- he could have.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Somebody wanted to give him an opportunity to leave the ghetto, but he wouldn't.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He went with the children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyway, I'm sorry that I'm so distracted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, the images crowd my head.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So things became progressively worse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after July, 1942, it was so bad that we had to find a hiding place for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what we did, we lived on the third floor-- in a third floor apartment.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the apartments, you know, the same apartments correspond to each other on the same side.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there was one room where my father worked that was covered with a chifferobe, you know, a closet.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have built-in closets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was covered with that, and this is where we hid.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But all the apartments, all the corresponding apartments, did the same thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The same trick was played.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, we put some-- covered that wall.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a kind of ruse to pretend that this is all that there is.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There's no other room.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were very fortunate to escape many of the roundups.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, in fact, when we studied, we studied every day in-- at this point, we didn't study anymore.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was impossible to go to school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my father read to us Yiddish books.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Every night, he read to us Yiddish books of the great writers like Peretz, Shalom Aleichem, and all the others, actually, throughout the period.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
